there are two types project management and work organization methods
        - kanban method
        - scrum method
kanban - it is a project management and work organization method that visualizes the work on boards. it uses a cards or sticky notes to respresent the task and these cards move through 
different stages ('to-do', 'in progress', 'done') to show the progress of the work.
scrum -  Scrum is an agile framework for managing and developing projects. It breaks work into fixed-length iterations called sprints, typically 2-4 weeks long
